// Fires when the D1 index database approaches its 10 GB hard cap — threshold at
// 7 GB (the plan's warning level, where the escape hatches kick in: tighten
// truncation caps -> drop tool_use input from FTS -> shard blocks+FTS by year).
//
// Source: the hub watchdog cron (*/15) emits, once per run, a structured log
//   { event: "hub.d1.db_size_bytes", bytes: <n> }
// (hub/src/cron/watchdog.ts, best-effort via PRAGMA page_count * page_size).
// Workers observability ships it to Log Analytics OTelLogs (Body = that JSON) —
// same path and column as missed-heartbeat.kql (verified live 2026-07-17).
//
// A 1h window comfortably contains a watchdog emission (it runs every 15 min);
// we take the most recent reported size and fire if it exceeds 7 GiB. Unlike
// missed-heartbeat.kql this needs no pipeline-silent sentinel: absence of a size
// reading is already covered by that alert's __pipeline_silent__ row.

OTelLogs
| where TimeGenerated > ago(1h)
| extend body = todynamic(Body)
| where body.event == "hub.d1.db_size_bytes"
| summarize arg_max(TimeGenerated, bytes = tolong(body.bytes))
| where bytes > 7 * 1024 * 1024 * 1024
| project TimeGenerated, bytes
